BOVINE SPONGIFORM ENCEPHALOPATHY IN SLOVAKIA:
Confirmation of the second case
---------------------------------
See also: 2 Nov 2001, 12 Oct 2001, 28 Sep 2001
Information received on 5 Nov 2001 from Prof. Dusan Magic, Chief Veterinary
Officer, State Veterinary Administration, Bratislava:
End of previous report period: 31 Oct 2001 (see Disease Information, 14
[44, 251, dated 2 Nov 2001).
End of this report period: 5 Nov 2001.
Location of the outbreak: Lucenec district.
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species / susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
bov / 509 / 1 / 0 / 63 / 0
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: the State Veterinary Institute in
Zvolen and the Central BSE Reference Laboratory in Bratislava.
B. Diagnostic tests used: Western blot (Prionics Check) and Platelia-BSE
Bio-Rad tests.
Source of agent / origin of infection: not yet known; investigation in
progress into the feed used on the farm.
Control measures during reporting period: in the herd of origin,
eradication by the "cohort cull" method. It was found that the confirmed
case had no living offspring.
